From: Chinmoy Dey <chinmoy@nexthop.ai>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] Integrate leak-detection handlers

Register the standard DMTF LeakDetection / LeakDetectorCollection /
LeakDetector route handlers.

These resources are NOT a SONiC OEM extension -- they implement standard
Redfish schemas that upstream bmcweb bundles but does not serve. The
handler source lives at the repo root (leak_detection/) and is copied
into bmcweb at build time by the Makefile (copy-leak-detection target).
This patch only wires it into route registration, independently of the
SONiC OEM integration (patch 0003):

 * redfish.cpp: include leak_detection/leak_detection.hpp and call
   requestRoutesLeakDetection()

Routes added:
 - GET /redfish/v1/Chassis/<id>/ThermalSubsystem/LeakDetection
 - GET /redfish/v1/Chassis/<id>/LeakDetectors[/<detectorId>]            (canonical)
 - GET /redfish/v1/Chassis/<id>/ThermalSubsystem/LeakDetection/LeakDetectors[/<detectorId>] (deprecated)
---
 redfish-core/src/redfish.cpp | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/redfish-core/src/redfish.cpp b/redfish-core/src/redfish.cpp
index abcdef3..1234569 100644
--- a/redfish-core/src/redfish.cpp
+++ b/redfish-core/src/redfish.cpp
@@ -20,6 +20,7 @@
 #include "fabric_ports.hpp"
 #include "fan.hpp"
 #include "hypervisor_system.hpp"
+#include "leak_detection/leak_detection.hpp"
 #include "log_services.hpp"
 #include "manager_diagnostic_data.hpp"
 #include "manager_logservices_dbus_eventlog.hpp"
@@ -247,5 +248,7 @@ RedfishService::RedfishService(App& app)
     requestRoutesRedfish(app);

     requestRoutesOpenBmcManager(*this);

+    requestRoutesLeakDetection(app);
+
     validate();
